                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d226">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12745: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-02T11:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 2, 1941—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 3—9:11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>859. Reference my number 627, May 31, 4 p.m.<note n="29" xml:id="d226fn29">Not
                        printed.</note> This morning’s press announces the appointment of General
                    Wavell, Commander-in-Chief Middle East, as Commander-in-Chief India, replacing
                    General Claude Auchinleck who becomes Commander-in-Chief Middle East. The
                    appointment is also announced of Captain Oliver Lyttelton as member of the War
                    Cabinet which he will represent in the Middle East.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
